<title>SWITZERLAND: Ciba sees higher 1996 profit.</title>
<headline>Ciba sees higher 1996 profit.</headline>
<dateline>BASLE, Switzerland 1996-10-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>Ciba-Geigy AG said it still expected to report a higher 1996 full-year profit, but without taking into account the costs of planning and preparing for its planned merger with Sandoz AG and the spin-off of specialty chemicals operations.</p>
<p>&quot;Without taking into account the costs of planning and preparing the merger with Sandoz, and the spin-off of the specialty chemicals business, Ciba still expects an increased profit for the current year,&quot; the company said in its nine-month sales report.  </p>
<p>Ciba and Sandoz announced plans lasts March to merge to form the second most powerful company in the industry. The merger is pending U.S. Federal Trade Commission approval.</p>
<p>Ciba reported a 1995 group net profit of 2.156 billion Swiss francs on turnover of 10.70 billion.</p>
